history.content: 161 is not being offered in the Spring. So the first schedule.

children.subject: do you know what is the workload of cs 162 if taken if a good group ?
<md>Quite heavy. 30 hours per project per person is to be expected. 10 hours if your group is really good (and you yourself are quite good)</md>
<md>CS 162 is helpful for recruiting. Not sure what 194-26 is. The less classes you take while recruiting, the better it generally is</md>

history.content:
Hello,

I'm a transfer student, and 2021-2022 is going to be my last. I have taken 61a, 61b, 61c, 70, 16a, 16b, 100, and 170 so far. Since I'm going to apply for full time job next Fall, I'm wondering which schedule below is better for the Fall recruiting. For reference, I have gotten As in all of my classes, and these are the classes that I want to take before graduation. I decide to take Prob 140 instead of EE 126 since I don't have much interested in the last 1/3 of the class.

This semester, I'm doing cs 61c, cs 170 and ee 16b, and it went pretty well. However, I started slacking off after spring break, so now I was playing catching up :(

Fall: Prob 140, CS 161, CS 194-26

Spring: CS 162, CS 189

vs

Fall: CS 162, CS 194-26

Spring: Prob 140, CS 161, CS 189

Thank you very much !

Update: I asked on 61c, and the course staffs replied there is a very good chance the class is going to be offered in the Spring if this semester and next semester goes well. If it's not offered, then I'm going to take a class with similar workload to CS 161 such as CS 186 or CS 171 in the Spring. Is prob 140, cs 194-26, cs 161 easier than 162, 194-26 ?
